about.summary: Query and print information about the current R session. It is similar to 'utils::sessionInfo()', but includes more information about packages, and where they were installed from.

name: r-sessioninfo
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.1.1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-sessioninfo
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/sessioninfo_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/sessioninfo/sessioninfo_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 166b04678448a7decd50f24afabe5e2ad613e3c55b180ef6e8dd7a870a1dae48

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1002
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:

  host:
    - r-base
    - r-cli
    - r-withr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-cli
    - r-withr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('sessioninfo')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('sessioninfo')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/r-lib/sessioninfo#readme
  license: GPL-2
  summary: Query and print information about the current R session. It is similar to 'utils::sessionInfo()',
    but includes more information about packages, and where they were installed from.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - johanneskoester
    - bgruening
    - daler
    - jdblischak
    - cbrueffer
    - roryk
    - dbast
